Method Reference
=================
these are shorthand notation for lambda expression.
works only for the lambda expressions
syntax: className::methodName or obj::methodName


static method ref                                        || className::staticMethodName
instance method for particular object                    || refName::methodName
instance method of arbitrary object of a particular type || ClassName :: methodName
constructor method ref                                   || syntax : ClassName::new

orbitertay object(Un bound) : the object will not be fixed in advance.
Instead each obj will be provided at runtime.
Bounded Object : Bound method reference means is the object  is already known and fixed at the time of reference created.